Microneedling is considered a fractional modality since only portions of skin are affected, leaving bridges of untreated skin behind. This allows for quicker healing, better results with less downtime, and lowered chance of complications. Aggressive methods for scar revision often leave clients with a waxy appearance due to the formation of scar tissue to heal the dramatic wound. Microneedling decreases growth factors that are associated with scar tissue and increases those associated with scarless healing, allowing for natural results. ⁠
